      <trans-unit id="10988" identifier="a4adec0aaaba7c1c6402ab5f49f51dd7">
        <source>{panel type=&quot;ct-decomposition&quot; title=&quot;Decomposition&quot;}</source>
        <target>crwdns10988:0crwdne10988:0</target>
        <note>Context: Paragraph text&#13;
XPath: /p[9]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10989" identifier="b8059ec2d03a23eb629f5072c0a8b54b">
        <source>To accomplish this task students must decompose the process “find the error”
into smaller steps.</source>
        <target>crwdns10989:0crwdne10989:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[10]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10990" identifier="1e4503bf6f3e2fe8489455e2ab9e74ab">
        <source>The first step students break it down to could be “look at each row, one by
one, until I find an error”.</source>
        <target>crwdns10990:0crwdne10990:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[10]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10991" identifier="cebcb4f0d7099d974fb30bcd73de4cef">
        <source>Students can break it down further, focusing on one row, and asking themselves
whether the row has an even or odd number of black cards.</source>
        <target>crwdns10991:0crwdne10991:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[10]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10992" identifier="0d192d7300b3834476c8ae08a2869139">
        <source>They are decomposing the bigger problem down to a subtask, which they can then
work through and move closer to completing the full problem.</source>
        <target>crwdns10992:0crwdne10992:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[10]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10993" identifier="a7ca72b69b04df41f21e9ebf6a497086">
        <source>Likewise when they need to find the column with an error they can break this
down in the same way, focusing on one column, and asking the same question
above: does the column have an even or odd number of black cards?</source>
        <target>crwdns10993:0crwdne10993:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[10]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10994" identifier="8e67878d98fddbf22dcc4a0afee0e794">
        <source>These processes are much simpler to solve that the big problem “Find the
error”, but if you work through them all then you will have completely solved
that big problem!</source>
        <target>crwdns10994:0crwdne10994:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[10]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10995" identifier="833d815031c5d5819a2b19b8c4affd40">
